With this definition of multiplication and addition, familiar rules for the arithmetic of rational or real numbers continue to hold for complex numbers. More precisely, the distributive property, the commutative properties (of addition and multiplication) hold. Therefore, the complex numbers form an algebraic structure known as a &quot;field&quot;, the same way as the rational or real numbers do.

===Complex conjugate, absolute value, argument and division===
