Hypercomplex numbers also generalize formula_54 formula_43 formula_56 and formula_57 For example, this notion contains the split-complex numbers, which are elements of the ring formula_58 (as opposed to formula_59 for complex numbers). In this ring, the equation has four solutions.

The field formula_42 is the completion of formula_61 the field of rational numbers, with respect to the usual absolute value metric. Other choices of metrics on formula_62 lead to the fields formula_63 of -adic numbers (for any prime number ), which are thereby analogous to formula_45. There are no other nontrivial ways of completing formula_62 than formula_42 and formula_67 by Ostrowski&#x27;s theorem. The algebraic closures formula_68 of formula_63 still carry a norm, but (unlike formula_3) are not complete with respect to it. The completion formula_71 of formula_68 turns out to be algebraically closed. By analogy, the field is called -adic complex numbers.

The fields formula_54 formula_67 and their finite field extensions, including formula_43 are called local fields.

